Company Overview of Schwartz Investment Trust - Schwartz Value Focused Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Schwartz Investment Trust - Schwartz Value Focused Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Schwartz Investment Counsel, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. The fund employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as price of stocks in relation to cash flow, earnings, dividends, book value, asset value, changes in operations, management, capital allocation, and strategies or product offerings to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Standa...
Schwartz Investment Trust - Schwartz Value Focused Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Schwartz Investment Counsel, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. The fund employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as price of stocks in relation to cash flow, earnings, dividends, book value, asset value, changes in operations, management, capital allocation, and strategies or product offerings to create its portfolio. It benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the Standard & Poor’s 1500 Index. The fund was formerly known as Schwartz Investment Trust - Schwartz Value Fund. Schwartz Investment Trust - Schwartz Value Focused Fund was formed on January 1, 1984 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


