Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Value Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 11:27 AM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Value Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Value Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Schwartz Investment Counsel, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. The fund invests in stocks of companies that offer products or services or engage in practices that do not violate the core values and teachings of the Roman Catholic Church and does socially responsible investing. It employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as cash flow, earnings, dividends, book value, asset value, changes in...
Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Value Fund is an open-ended equity mutual fund launched and managed by Schwartz Investment Counsel, Inc. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across all market capitalizations. The fund invests in stocks of companies that offer products or services or engage in practices that do not violate the core values and teachings of the Roman Catholic Church and does socially responsible investing. It employs fundamental analysis focusing on factors such as cash flow, earnings, dividends, book value, asset value, changes in operations, management, capital allocation, strategies, and product offerings to create its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of its portfolio against the S&P Midcap 400 Index. It does not invest in stocks of companies involved in the practice of abortion, distribution of pornographic material, those that contribute corporate funds to Planned Parenthood, or those that support embryonic stem cell research. The fund was formerly known as Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Catholic Values Fund. Schwartz Investment Trust - Ave Maria Value Fund was formed on May 1, 2001 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


801 West Ann Arbor TrailSuite 244Plymouth, MI 48170United StatesFounded in 2001



Phone: 734-455-7777

Fax: 734-455-7720

